channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 9/11 families call on Trump, Harris to oppose US-Saudi deal until kingdom admits involvement in terror attack
item.description: More than 3,000 family members of 9/11 victims are demanding Trump and Harris oppose any peace deal with Saudi Arabia unless the Kingdom acknowledges its involvement in the attack.

item.title: Trump, Harris gear up for highly anticipated debate
item.description: The last time former President Donald Trump was on a debate stage, he ended President Biden's political career.

item.title: Do We Have Any Courage Left?
item.description: A hard but necessary question.

item.title: Courts Order RFK Jr. To Be Removed From Ballots In North Carolina And Michigan
item.description: The legal wins for Kennedy could help the Trump campaign in the key swing states.

item.title: Dems face tight timeline to confirm Biden-Harris judges, surpass Trump legacy
item.description: Democrats face several obstacles in helping President Biden appoint more federal judges than former President Trump did during his term.

item.title: Political books looking to grab a younger audience
item.description: Publishers are not overlooking politics as a way to appeal to a certain age group. An author and an artist have rushed to write and illustrate a new children's book, set to be released by Little, Brown Books for Young Readers on Oct. 29 -- just a week before election day.

item.title: San Francisco Should Try Punishing Criminals, Not Businesses
item.description: A new city ordinance mandating nightly business closures in the Tenderloin both fails to address the real problem and hampers economic opportunity.

item.title: Early Voting Season Begins Even As Some States Are Still Deciding Who’s On Their Ballots
item.description: Early voting ballots are being sent out even as numerous issues are still being settled.

item.title: House Dems issue response to GOP report on Biden's withdrawal from Afghanistan
item.description: The House Democrats on the Foreign Affairs Committee released their own memo on President Biden's chaotic 2021 withdrawal from Afghanistan after the GOP's report.

item.title: Cotton says Americans value records over endorsements
item.description: Sen. Tom Cotton says endorsements are not going to make or break the November election, after a former vice president became the highest-ranking Republican yet to support the Democratic presidential candidate.

item.title: The Nanny State Is Not the Answer to Parents’ Challenges
item.description: Yes, surgeon general, parents are stressed. But their lives are less lonely, more meaningful, and happier.

item.title: YouTube Uses DOJ Allegations To Justify Axing Tenet Media’s Channel Without Due Process
item.description: The widely used video platform YouTube removed Tenet Media and related channels from its services on Thursday after the Justice Department accused the company of partaking in a secret Russian influence operation. The revelation comes days after the Biden Department of Justice (DOJ) announced the seizure of nearly three dozen internet domains it alleged were […]

item.title: House GOP releases scathing report on Biden's withdrawal from Afghanistan
item.description: House Foreign Affairs Chair Mike McCaul released a scathing report from his committee on the 2021 Afghanistan withdrawal and highlighted areas of mismanagement.

item.title: Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders says Liz Cheney is 'in the minority' on being against Trump
item.description: Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders said former Rep. Liz Cheney is in a party of one when it comes to opposing former President Donald Trump.

item.title: The ‘Emergency’ Emergency
item.description: Governments should have power to confront genuine crises. But emergency governance shouldn’t become the norm.

item.title: Montana County Declares Wrong Winner After Failing To Compare Total Voters To Ballots
item.description: Election officials are not entirely sure what happened.

item.title: Democrats driving religious vote away from party as Trump courts Catholics: ‘Anti-Christian’ party
item.description: The Democratic Party is likely pushing away religious voters with "anti-Christian" policies such as abortion and transgender issues, while Trump courts the voting bloc.

item.title: Former Rep. Liz Cheney says she's a conservative but Trump is not
item.description: Former Rep. Liz Cheney on Sunday slammed former President Donald Trump as "not a conservative."

item.title: My Kingdom for a Key Lime Pie
item.description: A pie that’s worthy of royalty and couldn’t be simpler to make.

item.title: Democrats Are Terrified Of GOP Plan To Protect U.S. Election From Noncitizen Voting
item.description: Why are Democrats and their media mouthpieces so afraid of the GOP plan to keep noncitizens from voting in American elections?
